<% provide(:title, 'Get Started') %>
<div class="container-fluid">
	<div class="container">

		<!-- header -->
		<h2 class="section_header left"><span> Getting Started </span></h2>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span6">
				<i class="i_cloud"></i><h4> Free, Hosted Environment</h4>
				<p class="environments">
				<p>
					Megam is the easy way to manage your polygot apps on cloud. The cloud platform built using Chef and Scala/Akka.
					To see how Quickly you can get a polygot cloud app running, you can play in the
					<code>
						free sandbox
					</code>
					by
					<code>
						signing up an account
					</code>
					<% unless current_user %>
				<p>
					<%= link_to "Sign Up Now!", signup_path, :class => "btn btn-success btn-large" %>
				</p>
				<% end %>
			</div>
			<div class="span6">
				<i class="i_cloud"></i>
				<h4> Private Hosted Environment</h4>
				<p class="environments">
					For  Businesses that want to get involved in using it for their cloud move,
					there is a great set of installables with
					<code>
						instructions for you
					</code>
					to run from your
					<code>
						private hosted environment.
					</code>
				</p>
				<p>
					<%= link_to 'Installing Megam', "http://docs.megam.co/install", :class => 'btn btn-success btn-large' %>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		</br>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span12" align="center">
				<i class="i_cloud"></i><h4> Cloud Readiness</h4>
				<p class="environments">
					Read in this questionaire to see your PaaS readiness
					<h5> Megam a polygot PaaS is a cloud platform that can be tailored for your needs. </h5>
					<%= link_to "Am I Ready", "http://docs.megam.co/contactus", :class => "btn btn-info btn-large" %>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<h2 class="section_header left"><span>Learn About Megam</span></h2>
		<table class="table table-bordered table-striped table-hover">
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<td> Projects </td>
					<td> Help </td>
					<td> Code </td>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td>Cloud API Server</td>
					<td><%= link_to "Installing the Cloud API Server",   "http://docs.megam.co/install", { :target => '_blank'} %></td>
					<td><%= link_to "A Stateless Cloud API Server [Scala/Playframework]",   "https://github.com/indykish/megam_play.git", { :target => '_blank'} %></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Cloud Brdige Herk</td>
					<td><%= link_to "Installing the Cloud Bridge Herk",   "http://docs.megam.co/install", { :target => '_blank'} %></td>
					<td><%= link_to "Cloud Bridge to API Server and PubSub Agents",   "https://github.com/indykish/megam_akka.git", { :target => '_blank'} %></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>Cloud App Connector</td>
					<td><%= link_to "Installing the Cloud App Connector",   "http://docs.megam.co/install", { :target => '_blank'} %></td>
					<td><%= link_to "RESTful Cloud connectors to Salesforce, GoogleApp[Preview]",   "https://github.com/indykish/deccanplato.git", { :target => '_blank'} %></td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>
		</table>
		<!-- list -->

		<div id="faq" class="faq_page">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="span12">
					<i class="i_chart"></i>
					<h4>Quick Start </h4>
					<p>
						<div class="faq">
							<div class="number">
								1
							</div>
							<div class="question">
								What are the components of Megam ?
							</div>
							<div class="answer">
								There are three major components <span class="label label-info">Medium</span>,<span class="label label-info">Cloud API Server</span>, <span class="label label-info">Cloud Bridge Herk</span>
								</br>
								<span class="label">Medium</span>:The Medium can be WebApp built using Rails, CLI (Ruby) or Mob (Sencha Touch
								<code>
									* coming soon
								</code>
								).</br><span class="label">Cloud API Server      </span>: Cloud API Server is a RESTful Play(Scala) responsible for managing the description of cloud resources.
								</br>
								<span class="label">Cloud Bridge Herk</span>: Cloud Bridge Herk is an instrumentor by taking the cloud description and mediates between the PubSubEngine and the Cloud API Server
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="faq">
							<div class="number">
								2
							</div>
							<div class="question">
								I am an Administrator, I would like to try it On-Premise.
							</div>
							<div class="answer">
								Great. We would like to help you out. Give us a shout, we'll hand hold you.
								Read this questionaire, before you start (We'll provide an auto assessor `soon` for your hardware, private cloud,
								hybrid cloud, and infor your readiness)
								<br>
								<%= link_to "For further reading",   "http://docs.megam.co", { :target => '_blank'} %>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="faq">
							<div class="number">
								3
							</div>
							<div class="question">
								I am a Developer Great. How do I Quickly Launch Java for Staging ?
							</div>
							<div class="answer">
								There are screencasts in the <%= link_to "Tour",    page_path("tour"), { :target => '_blank'} %>
                                which walks thru on how quick you can launch a java app.
								<br>
								All you need is a GitHub project. Refer <%= link_to "Tour",    page_path("tour"), { :target => '_blank'} %>, if you need help <%= link_to "Contact Us",   page_path("contact_us"), { :target => '_self'} %>.
								<br>
								<%= link_to "For further reading.",   "http://docs.megam.co", { :target => '_blank'} %>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="faq">
							<div class="number">
								4
							</div>
							<div class="question">
								I am  DevOps Guy. What is the deal with Cloud Management ?
							</div>
							<div class="answer">
								There are many cookbooks curated for Chef 11 that runs in the public hosted sandbox of Megam Cloud. 
								<br>
								<br>
								Click here to see the  <%= link_to "chef-repo.",   "http://github.com/indykish/chef-repo.git", { :target => '_blank'} %>
								We don't support <code>Hosted Chef</code> yet, but we are testing it. If you wish to use our private 
								offering then you can install chef-server, and clone/tweak the chef-repo as you wish.
								<br>
								<%= link_to "For further reading.",   "http://docs.megam.co", { :target => '_blank'} %>
							</div>
						</div>
					</p>
				</div>
				<hr/>
				</br>
				<div class="span6">
					<% unless current_user %>
					<h3 align="center"> I have an account. </h3>
					<h4 align="center"> <%= link_to "Sign In Now!", signin_path, :class => "btn btn-info btn-large" %> </h4>
					<% end %>
				</div>
				<div class="span6">
					<%= image_tag "cloudshield.png", :alt => "cloud shield"%>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
